{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer"]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot15RenderingServerC14instanceCreateAA3RIDCyFZ","title":"instanceCreate()","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"instanceCreate","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot3RIDC","text":"RID"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Type Method","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/instanceCreate()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"instanceCreate"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot3RIDC","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RID","text":"RID","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once finished with your RID, you will want to free the RID using the RenderingServer’s "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/freeRid(_:)"},{"text":" method.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An instance is a way of placing a 3D object in the scenario. Objects like particles, meshes, reflection probes and decals need to be associated with an instance to be visible in the scenario using "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/instanceSetBase(instance:base:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The equivalent node is "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VisualInstance3D","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a visual instance and adds it to the RenderingServer. It can be accessed with the RID that is returned. This RID will be used in all "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"instance_*"},{"text":" RenderingServer functions.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/renderingserver\/instancecreate()"]}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/RenderingServer":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/renderingserver","title":"RenderingServer","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Server for anything visible.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"RenderingServer"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"RenderingServer"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer","role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/RenderingServer/instanceSetBase(instance:base:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"instanceSetBase"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"instance"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot3RIDC","text":"RID","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"base","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RID","kind":"typeIdentifier",